        "title": "AWS Services Overview",
        "content": "AWS offers a wide array of services, broadly categorized as:\n\n*   **Compute:** Services like EC2 (virtual servers) for running applications.\n*   **Storage:** Services like S3 (object storage) for storing data.\n*   **Databases:** Services like RDS (relational databases) and DynamoDB (NoSQL databases) for managing data.\n*   **Networking:** Services like VPC (virtual private cloud) for creating isolated networks.\n*   The 'AWS Explained' video provides a good overview of these services."
      },
